      • forceOnThisLevel

        @DomainSpecific
private static SublistManager.LevelStore.LevelTupleA forceOnThisLevel(java.lang.String numberText,
                                                                                      SublistManager.LevelStore.LevelTupleA inputTuple)
        Sets a force-flag if the paragraph to be inserted has to be on this current level, no matter what

        This happens with bulleted lists which cannot be more significant than an immediately preceding bulleted list, otherwise they would break the hierarchy.

        Parameters:
        numberText - numberText of the paragraph to be inserted
        inputTuple - currentTuple to check against
        Returns:
        the inputTuple, possibly in a wrapper class
        See Also:
        #isOnSameListLevel(String, LevelTuple, boolean)

      • isEqualLevels

        private static boolean isEqualLevels(java.lang.String[] levelString,
                                     SublistManager.LevelStore.LevelTuple startTuple,
                                     boolean startAtGivenLevel)
        Checks if the numberTexts of a given level hierarchy and an arbitrary array are (element-wise) equal
        Parameters:
        levelString - array with the last element representing the numberText of the least significant level
        startTuple - least significant tuple to base the comparison on
        startAtGivenLevel - if true start the comparison at startTuple; otherwise start at the parent of startTuple
        Returns:
        true if all elements of the levelString match the numberTexts of the startTuple and all its more significant predecessors; otherwise false
